# FreeCRM General Guidelines

## File Management
- **Do not create new files if possible** - prefer editing existing files
- **Never create aliases** like `class_alias()`

## Version Control
- **Never use git without consent** - ask the user before running any git command

## Bulk Editing
- **Use sed for multiple changes** - when performing many changes in a single file, use sed instead of individual edits

## Error Handling
- **Continue on errors** - if there are any errors during development, do not stop - continue with the task
- The application is resilient and partial fixes are valuable

## Agent Autonomy (Critical)
- **Do not ask the user to do work the model can do** (e.g., "tell me what files to check", "paste logs", "confirm obvious assumptions", "choose between equivalent options").
- **Assume and proceed**: pick the most reasonable approach, verify by reading code/rules/logs and running checks/tests, and adapt if evidence contradicts the assumption.
- **Only ask the user** when something truly requires human input (credentials not available, external approvals, CAPTCHAs/logins, destructive/irreversible actions requiring confirmation, missing proprietary context) or an important decision has to be made.

## Development Philosophy
- Prefer modifying existing code over creating new structures
- Keep the codebase maintainable and avoid unnecessary complexity
- Focus on incremental improvements

## Migrated Docker Server
- FreeCRM is deployed on `local.itconnect.pl` in `/opt/freecrm` and is available at `http://local.itconnect.pl/`.
- Connect as `bmankowski@local.itconnect.pl`; manage the stack with `docker compose` from `/opt/freecrm`.
- Services are `web`, `app`, `cron`, and `db`; MariaDB is bound to `127.0.0.1:3306` on the server.
- Background jobs: `docker compose up -d cron` runs `cron/vtigercron.php` every minute via supercronic (log: `cache/logs/cron.log`). No host crontab required.
- Runtime data lives in `/opt/freecrm/storage`; it was copied from production `10.0.0.220:/var/www/yetiforce/storage`.
- Migration backups are kept in `/opt/freecrm/_migration`, with local rollback dump under `tmp/migration-20260511-134258/`.
